@flexiarg process-coherence/is-this-even-a-problem
@title Ask "Is This Even a Problem?" Before Engaging the Machinery
@sigils [?/∅]
@keywords dissolved problem, already answered, energy budget, primary source, pointer-following, pre-check, cheap first, anti-minimization
@audience any process about to spend significant energy on a question
@tone corrective
@style pattern

! conclusion: Before spending significant energy evaluating, constructing, or optimizing over a question, check whether the question still EXISTS at current context: the answer may already be recorded in the primary documents, or the tension may have dissolved as surrounding work landed. Read the primary source and chase its pointers FIRST; engage the expensive machinery only where the documents run out.

  + context: Pipelines, evaluators, and selectors are built for questions that were live when they
    were wired. Questions dissolve — someone answers them in a doc, a prerequisite lands, a ruling
    changes the frame — but the machinery keeps running at full cost either way.

  + IF:
      A process (agent turn, evaluation lane, planning loop) is about to spend real energy on a
      question — which action, whether to construct, what this mission needs.

  + HOWEVER:
      The answer may already be written down (a status ruling, a checkpoint, a cross-referenced
      result), or the question may have dissolved since the machinery was pointed at it — and the
      machinery cannot notice, because retrieval-by-similarity paraphrases documents but does not
      FOLLOW their pointers.

  + THEN:
      Spend the cheap move first: read the primary document, follow the dependencies it names to
      their current state, and ask "is this even (still) a problem?" If the documents answer it,
      act on the answer and record it. Engage the expensive machinery only for what remains
      genuinely open after the reading.

  + BECAUSE:
      Energy spent re-deriving what is already recorded is anti-minimization — the machine version
      of a free-energy agent that never updates on its own futility. A loop that pays uses its
      expensive apparatus exactly where documents run out, and its cheap literacy everywhere else.
      (Seed pattern for cascade construction: most WM scenarios should START here — the first box
      of almost any process cascade is a reading, not a computation.)

  + canonical-instance:
      The honest-nothings arc, 2026-07-04: the cascade lane spent 674 arena ticks evaluating
      cascades that never won, folds abstaining by construction, over ψ scraps whose questions the
      mission documents had already answered — M-first-flights' next move (and its Phase-B arming)
      was written in its own body the whole time. Four reads and two greps found it; the pipeline
      structurally could not (E-live-loop-1 origin + S1; Flight 1 logs in p4ng/flights/).
